!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

pursue /pəˈsjuː/

(pursuing,pursued,pursues) 

1. V-T If you pursue an activity, interest, or plan, you carry it out or follow it. 执行; 贯彻 [正式] 

例： He said Japan would continue to pursue the policies laid down at the London summit. 他说日本将继续贯彻伦敦峰会上确定的方针。 

2. V-T If you pursue a particular aim or result, you make efforts to achieve it, often over a long period of time. 追求; 努力实现 [正式] 

例： He will pursue a trade policy that protects American workers. 他将努力实行保护美国工人的贸易政策。 

3. V-T If you pursue a particular topic, you try to find out more about it by asking questions. 追问 [正式] 

例： If your original request is denied, don't be afraid to pursue the matter. 如果你最初的要求被拒绝了，不要害怕去追问这件事情。 

4. V-T If you pursue a person, vehicle, or animal, you follow them, usually in order to catch them. 追赶 [正式] 

例： She pursued the man who had stolen a woman's bag. 她追赶那个偷了一女士钱包的男子。

